Teach by one pangram example instead of prose grammar

Founder's 'pangram' idea: one example that uses every letter ('the quick brown
fox...'). examples/pangram/pangram.kal uses EVERY type and construct, annotated;
read it once, write any pack by analogy — no grammar to carry.

- MCP: learn_by_example tool returns the pangram; server 'instructions' (sent
  once at handshake, not per request) point agents to it
- pangram embedded in the binary, guarded by a test that it COMPILES (never
  teaches wrong syntax); ~1.3k tokens, self-evident field syntax name: type
- preferred over get_grammar
